## IMPORTANT INSTRUCTIONS

1. Use SQLAlchemy with the existing PostgreSQL ENUMs вЂ” use String type in ORM to avoid ENUM conflicts, or properly reference existing PostgreSQL ENUMs
2. Do NOT use Alembic to create tables вЂ” tables already exist in PostgreSQL. Only set up Alembic for future migrations
3. Use dependency injection for DB session (get_db)
4. All endpoints must return proper HTTP status codes (200, 201, 404, 422, 500)
5. Use try/except in all endpoints with proper error messages
6. Add docstrings to all route functions (FastAPI uses these for Swagger docs)
7. All datetime fields should be timezone-aware
8. The /api/access/request endpoint is the most important вЂ” implement it with full logic as described above

Start by creating requirements.txt, then .env, then config.py, then database.py, then all models, then schemas, then routes, then main.py. Make sure everything connects correctly and the app runs with: uvicorn app.main:app --reload